The paper deals with the problem of optimizing algorithms for combinatorial partitioning problems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and optimization. The paper specifically focuses on learning algorithms for clustering, max-cut, and integer quadratic programming, which are all topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning and optimization communities. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
